de, Österreich, Bosnien-Herzegowina, die Schweiz, die Türkei und Israel ergänzt. Kurze Portraits, in denen ausgewählte TrialogInitiativen beispielhaft mit ihren Programmen, Profilen und Kontaktdaten vorgestellt werden, vervollständigen die Studie.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2022) 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / General.2bisacsh  aChristentum.  aGesellschaft.  aIntegration.  aIslam.  aJudentum.  aMigration.  aReligion.  aSozialkapital.1 aHinterhuber, Eva Maria, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aManteuffel, Marie von, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aStrachwitz, Rupert Graf, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Social Sciences 2000 - 2014z9783110638080oZDB-23-GSS08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruyterteBook-Paket Best of Lucius & Luciusz97831105150770 cprintz978382820467640uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978382826011540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783828260115423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783828260115/original  a978-3-11-051507-7  eBook-Paket Best of Lucius & Lucius  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA12STME  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-GSSc2000d2014